        <td width="500" height="18" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#993333" class="box_titles">Things just keep getting better and better <span class="box_titles_small">February 18, 2005, 04:42:02 PM by <a href="mailto:noah@uberyou.com">Noah</a></span>		</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="763" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#996666" class="box_links">
		<center><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/King Zalak the Ancient.jpg" alt="" style="border:none;" /border=0 width=700 height=525></center><br /><center><B>King Zalak the Ancient</B><center><br /><br /><br />Since the Launch of EQ2 we have seen the world change a lot.  The developers work hard to fix issues at the same time release new and exciting adventures for players.  The last big patch, <a href=http://fohguild.org/eq2/forums/viewtopic.php?t=81>Live Update #3</a>, made some well needed adjustments to the game.  The addition of 4 new dungeons has made it possible for us to have something to do everynight (see above our crack team putting the hurt on King Zalak the Ancient).  At the same time a few of our dragons (/wave Vox and Vene!) have been adjusted to reasonable encounters but still challenging.<br /><br /><br />We toyed with the new zones for a bit (see above pic of us putting the hurt down on one of the new named, nice GFXs!) but nothing is like slaying a dragon.  Nearly a month ago we took down Venekor.  Ever since he got a hold of some crack, the chinese money farmers could not be saved from his tyranny of CT.  Since we love our Team Dugim, FoH put an end to Venekor's reign of Cazic Thule.<br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/venekorv2down.jpg" alt="" style="border:none;" /border=0 width=700 height=525><br /><br /><br />Since we were stumped by this mob for so long, I thought I'd show everyone the Venekor strat from the FoH playbook - <a href=http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/gallery/albums/userpics/10016/normal_Venekor%20Strat.JPG>Priest Hex Pattern</a>.  His loot wasn't great but Grats Nyco on <a href=http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/gallery/albums/userpics/10016/enchanted%20cedar%20wand.JPG>ancient cedar wand</a> !<br /><br /><br />Of course, the usual x2 and x4 mobs were taken down.  Aphyxia, Vaz, Nagalik, Fist, Kar'thuk... etc etc all farmed down giving a few of our members some nice items.<br /><br /><br /><a href=http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/gallery/albums/userpics/10016/black%20ebon%20chain%20gloves.JPG>black ebon chainmail gloves</a> - Grats Mystique<br /><a href=http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/gallery/albums/userpics/10016/Gloves%20of%20Madness.JPG>Gloves of Madness</a> - Grats Purrzephany<br /><a href=http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/gallery/albums/userpics/10016/thumb_Spiritbound%20Chain%20Coif.JPG>Spiritbound Chain Coif</a> - Grats Skorge<br /><a href=http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/gallery/albums/userpics/10016/thumb_Ancient%20Ancestral%20Gloves.JPG>Ancient Ancestral Gloves</a> - Grats Alloria<br />Uber BP I have no pic of - Grat Linyen (pst him for link)<br /><br /><br />Now usually there is no "Quotes" section on these News Updates.  Due to people bugging me to put up some funny shit I have taken a few SShots to display.  More will come later when people actually say funny or stupid shit.<br /><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/Funny quotes Part 1.JPG" alt="" style="border:none;" /><br /><br /><br /><br />-Noah Notfuror
		<p>  :: <a href="/eq2/index.php?action=fullnews&amp;showcomments=1&amp;id=9">Comments (0)</a> ::  
[<a href="#top">top</a>]</p>			
		</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
	<br />
<table width="763" border="0">
      <tr>
        <td width="500" height="18" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#993333" class="box_titles">The crap you get raiding at 50..... <span class="box_titles_small">February 12, 2005, 01:02:33 AM by <a href="mailto:noah@uberyou.com">Noah</a></span>		</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="763" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#996666" class="box_links">
		So you get to 50 and hope to have some shit you can raid.  Yeah, you know, those big ass mobs you see in zones with lvl 55 x8324 ++++++ above their name and 18 adds, WUWU shit to do!!  You get 24 of the best players around, drag these people into the depths of Sol Eye and other places, and what do you get??  Oh yes, the infamous <B>WOODEN BOX!!!</B><br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/Nagaliks Head.JPG" alt="" style="border:none;" /><br /><br /><br />......... never heard him say that before.  Little did we know what to expect when Mezmith disarmed the trap successfully but still did the puke emote.<br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/wood box.JPG" alt="" style="border:none;" /><br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/Nagacrap.JPG" alt="" style="border:none;" /><br /><br /><br />It is NO WAY acceptable that a mob that is in the middle of east bumF*#@ x4+++ 55th lvl drops 8 pieces of shit that you will vendor for 2gp.  It is bad enough that you get ONE piece of decent loot in a metal chest from a x4 mob.  But to get a wooden box of shit is just absurd!   Now you can see we might be a bit pissed about this... it probably has to do with the fact that this was the THIRD raid mob in a row to drop a steamer.  <br /><br />Hear us now: EVERY x4 MOB NEEDS TO DROP A METAL BOX EVERYTIME.  You don't raid to get a bunch of shit loot.  You don't spend hours upon hours of strat discussion to get a TEAK CUDGLE and some crap Adepts that some noob has set for 20gp on the broker.  You raid the big stuff to get the big stuff.  <br /><br />Since we killed everything that can be raided in a matter of 2 days (oh yes, 7+ days or more before anything will pop...yay harvesting here I come /hug Dave), I have had some extra time on my hands to do a theraputic comic to make light of our woes.<br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/Bad loot cartoon.jpg" alt="" style="border:none;" /><br /><br />I am sure the fellas from the BBurrow, Unrest, Grobb and Najena servers that I chat with will get a good laff.  Just know you're not alone.<br /><br />~Noah Notfuror
		<p>  :: <a href="/eq2/index.php?action=fullnews&amp;showcomments=1&amp;id=8">Comments (5)</a> ::  
[<a href="#top">top</a>]</p>			
		</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
	<br />
